I called to explain the missing items and was told “it’s not our fault, we can’t see the order on the machine like the kitchen sees.” I asked for a credit to the credit card for the missing items and was told they couldn’t do that since the order was made online. On top of it all the food was so-so. Don’t waster your time or money here.

I enjoy Don Pollo a lot, and it's my favorite fast food (especially on a lazy Sunday) but today the chicken and yuca weren't with that gold crisp. The chicken had shallow crispy parts but mostly looked weirdly pale. It was cooked, but the outside of the chicken didn't have that rich golden flavor, along with the yuca. The yuca is always mildly crispy and golden, but today it was VERY soft and pale. I decided to eat it, considering I already PAID FOR IT, but it was very disappointing how they decided the color of the meal was alright.

Honestly, I was kind of underwhelmed by Don Pollo. The chicken was good, sure, but it is not as good as some other similar places I've been to in the DC area (namely Crisp & Juicy).  The sides were pretty mediocre and didn't really add much to my meal.  The restaurant is small and doesn't have a lot of places to sit, so it may get over-crowded if too many people come for lunch/dinner.  Overall, I think you could find a better place in Bethesda to eat at, but it's not half bad. Just don't expect anything amazing.

I have been eating Peruvian chicken around DC for years and while this is not THE best,   pretty darn good. They are also super friendly and a whole chicken with sides that feeds 2 adults and 2 kids is about $20, which for Bethesda is an amazing deal and makes it our goto spot for when no one wants to cook!

Don Pollo serves tasty Peruvian chicken, liberally seasoned and roasted to juicy deliciousness. Sides are equally as tasty: fries are big and soft, rice and beans are terrific, and plantains are ripe and sweet. The space could stand a freshening. Loud music blares above which is somewhat off putting, as is the service that isn't interested in answering questions or giving menu suggestions.

Simply put, awesome!  Delicious, fresh and speedy.  Hard to find a better meal under $10 in Bethesda.
I LOVE Don Pollo. Service is fast, food is delicious, and the price is right. For $7-$8 dollars, you get delicious chicken, two sides, and a soda.
I've gotten takeout from here several times and the food is always great.  Tender moist chicken, tasty sauces, and friend yucca.  Definitely worth a stop in to indulge in some well made chicken.

I've been working in the neighborhood for a while, and that was my favorite place for a quick lunch. The chicken was always tasty, perfectly seasoned and roasted, and the speed of service was outstanding - by the time you are done with the cashier and picked up your sauces and cutlery, your meal is already being assembled in front of your eyes. Inexpensive, too.
